# PHOENIX PROJECT RULES - MAIN INDEX

This file is the **main index** for workspace rules under **`.cursor/rules/`**. Files live in **thematic subfolders** (not only the rules root).

## Thematic layout

| Folder | Path | Contents |
|--------|------|----------|
| **main** | `.cursor/rules/main/` | `core_rules.mdc` (Rule 0.x), `clarification_and_confidence.mdc` (Rule CONF.0), `phoenix.mdc` (this index) |
| **safety** | `.cursor/rules/safety/` | `safety_rules.mdc` |
| **agents** | `.cursor/rules/agents/` | `agent_rules.mdc` |
| **workflows** | `.cursor/rules/workflows/` | `workflow_rules.mdc`, `handsoff_playwright_report.mdc`, `playwright_detailed_reporting.mdc` |
| **workspace** | `.cursor/rules/workspace/` | `file_organization_rules.mdc`, `test_cases_structure.mdc` |
| **integrations** | `.cursor/rules/integrations/` | `database_workflow.mdc`, `energots_branch_lock.mdc`, `production_data_reader.mdc`, `jira_bug_agent.mdc`, `jira_rest_fallback.mdc`, `phoenix_branch_switching.mdc` |

**Additional (optional):** `Cursor-Project/config/cursorrules/autonomous_rules.md` — autonomous-operation notes if present.

## Rules loading

Cursor loads **all** `.mdc` files under `.cursor/rules/` **recursively** (subject to Cursor `globs` / `alwaysApply`). **Rule 0.0** (tiered): always honor injected `alwaysApply` rules; before **substantive** work, read the **canonical** SKILL/agent for that workflow (`Cursor-Project/docs/RULES_CANONICAL_INDEX.md`); full recursive `.mdc` audit only for explicit rules audits, **`validate-cursor-rules.ps1`**, or broad rule edits — see **`core_rules.mdc`** Rule 0.0.

## Quick reference (canonical paths)

- **Rule 0.x:** `.cursor/rules/main/core_rules.mdc`
- **Clarification / confidence gate:** `.cursor/rules/main/clarification_and_confidence.mdc` (Rule CONF.0)
- **Agents:** `.cursor/rules/agents/agent_rules.mdc`
- **Safety:** `.cursor/rules/safety/safety_rules.mdc`
- **Workflows:** `.cursor/rules/workflows/workflow_rules.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/workflows/handsoff_playwright_report.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/workflows/playwright_detailed_reporting.mdc`
- **Files / test cases layout:** `.cursor/rules/workspace/file_organization_rules.mdc`, `.cursor/rules/workspace/test_cases_structure.mdc`
- **DB / Git / EnergoTS / Prod / Jira (bug agent + REST read fallback) / Phoenix branch switching:** `.cursor/rules/integrations/*.mdc`
- **Slack reporting (three paths):** `Cursor-Project/config/template/Slack_reporting_paths.md` — short **Slack text** + **attach** detailed `.md` (`Cursor-Project/config/slack/upload-file-to-slack.ps1`)
- **Workspace patterns (architecture):** `Cursor-Project/docs/WORKSPACE_PATTERNS.md` · **Rule → canon map:** `Cursor-Project/docs/RULES_CANONICAL_INDEX.md`

## ⚠️ CRITICAL REMINDERS

1. **Rule 0.0:** Tiered rules loading — see **`core_rules.mdc`**; canonical map: **`Cursor-Project/docs/RULES_CANONICAL_INDEX.md`**. **Rule CONF.0:** If scope/environment/target/success criteria are ambiguous → ask before substantive action; do not guess (`clarification_and_confidence.mdc`).
2. **Rule 0.1:** ALWAYS end responses with "Agents involved: [names]"
3. **Rule 0.2:** ALL Phoenix questions → PhoenixExpert ONLY
4. **Rule 0.6:** Disk reports **only** when mandated (e.g. HandsOff), **`/report`**, **`/feedback`**, or explicit user save — default **chat-first**; full text: **`core_rules.mdc`** Rule 0.6
5. **Rule 0.8:** Phoenix never edited by AI; EnergoTS only EnergoTSTestAgent in `tests/`; all other workspace paths editable when user requests (provisional) — see `.cursor/rules/safety/safety_rules.mdc` Rule 7
6. **Rule 1:** GitLab and Confluence are READ-ONLY
7. **Rule 8:** ALWAYS consult PhoenixExpert before tasks
8. **Rule 11 / 0.3:** External automation may use IntegrationService; in Cursor chat follow MCP/Jira/GitLab steps — no `agents.*` imports here
9. **Rule 32:** ALL bug validation → ALWAYS use BugFinderAgent
10. **Rule 35/35a:** Test cases → cross-dependency-finder FIRST; Rule 35a: **Jira + codebase + shallow Confluence** — **no** local merge/git or git snapshot for cross-dep (see `workflow_rules.mdc`)
10a. **Rule 42 / JIRA.1:** Jira issue reads — **MCP first**; if Jira MCP fails after retries, use **REST read fallback** — **`.cursor/rules/integrations/jira_rest_fallback.mdc`**
11. **Rule 36:** Run Playwright tests from EnergoTS → energo-ts-run workflow ONLY; run only from `cursor` branch (Rule ENERGOTS.0)
11a. **Rule PHOENIX-SWITCH.0:** Before environment-sensitive Phoenix code reading (Q&A, bug validation, cross-dep, test-case generation, HandsOff), align every `Cursor-Project/Phoenix/*` repo to the matching `origin/<branch>` via `.cursor/commands/switch-phoenix-branches.ps1`; local Phoenix edits are discarded; Phoenix files stay READ-ONLY (Rule 0.8 Tier A) — see `.cursor/rules/integrations/phoenix_branch_switching.mdc`
12. **Rule 37:** Jira ticket + /HandsOff or !HandsOff → ALWAYS run full HandsOff flow (hands-off command/orchestrator); report named after Jira key + send to Slack to tester
12a. **Slack paths:** Bug validation (Rule 32) vs HandsOff vs scoped Playwright Slack — **`Cursor-Project/config/template/Slack_reporting_paths.md`** (do not merge; bug-validator workflow untouched)
13. **Rule JIRA.0:** Jira bug agent → Experiments board ONLY; NEVER create bugs in Phoenix delivery
14. **Rule PDR.0:** Production data questions → ALWAYS use ProductionDataReaderAgent
15. **Rule 34:** ALL agents MUST be organized in subdirectories

